-- U.A.E.’s Central Bank Will Cap Card Interest, Al-Khaleej Says
-- B y   Z a i n a b   F a t t a h
-- 2012-01-31T05:16:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/u-a-e-s-central-bank-will-cap-card-interest-al-khaleej-says.html
The United Arab Emirates’ Central
Bank will cap credit-card interest at less than 18 percent
annually,  Al-Khaleej newspaper  reported, citing an unidentified
central bank official.  Banks currently charge 27 percent to 36 percent annually.
The cap will be included in new rules the central bank has
completed and will announce in February, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
